                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/56: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-03T14:00:00-00:44">August 3, 1929—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:15 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>37. Referring to my cable of July 26, midnight. Ross states that charges
                            are unfounded and he would welcome a full and complete investigation
                            conditions of Firestone labor.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi></signed></closer>
